revision.text:
{{unsourced|date=January 2014}} {{Infobox summit | summit_name = Arab League Summit | other_titles = | image = Nasser-Faisal-Arafat-1970.jpg | caption = [[Gamal Abdel Nasser]] of [[Egypt]] (left), [[Faisal of Saudi Arabia]] (center), [[Yasser Arafat]] of [[Palestine Liberation Organization|Palestine]] (right) | country = [[Egypt]] | venues = | cities = [[Cairo]] | date = {{Start date|1970|09|27}} | website = }} The '''1970 Arab League summit''' was held on September 27 in [[Cairo]], [[Egypt]] as an extraordinary [[Arab League Summit]]. The summit came in the aftermath of the bloody events of [[Black September in Jordan]], and the clashes between the [[Palestinian Liberation Organization]] and King [[Hussein of Jordan]]. Egyptian president [[Gamal Abdul Nasser]] succeeded in getting both King Hussein of Jordan and [[Yasser Arafat]], the chairman of the [[PLO]], to end the bloody battle between Jordanians and the [[Palestinian fedayeen]]. The summit concluded its work on September 28, hours before Nasser died. The summit was boycotted by [[Iraq]], [[Syria]], [[Algeria]] and [[Morocco]].
