==Events== *[[1528]] &ndash; [[Gustav I of Sweden]] is crowned king of Sweden, having already reigned since his election in June 1523. *[[1554]] &ndash; [[Bayinnaung]], who would go on to assemble the largest empire in the history of Southeast Asia, is crowned [[List of Burmese monarchs|King of Burma]]. *[[1616]] &ndash; The city of [[Belém]], Brazil is founded on the [[Amazon River]] delta, by Portuguese captain [[Francisco Caldeira Castelo Branco]]. *[[1808]] &ndash; [[John Rennie the Elder|John Rennie]]'s scheme to defend [[St Mary's Church, Reculver]], founded in 669, from [[coastal erosion]] is abandoned in favour of demolition, despite the church being an exemplar of [[Anglo-Saxon architecture]] and [[Anglo-Saxon art|sculpture]]. * 1808 &ndash; The organizational meeting leading to the creation of the [[Wernerian Natural History Society]], a former Scottish learned society, is held in Edinburgh. *[[1848]] &ndash; The [[Sicilian revolution of 1848|Palermo rising]] takes place in [[Sicily]] against the [[House of Bourbon|Bourbon]] [[Kingdom of the Two Sicilies]]. *[[1866]] &ndash; The [[Royal Aeronautical Society]] is formed in London. *[[1872]] &ndash; [[Yohannes IV]] is crowned Emperor of [[Ethiopia]] in [[Axum]], the first imperial coronation in that city in over 200 years. *[[1895]] &ndash; [[National Trust for Places of Historic Interest or Natural Beauty|The National Trust]] is founded in the United Kingdom. *[[1908]] &ndash; A long-distance [[Radio broadcasting#History|radio]] message is sent from the [[Eiffel Tower]] for the first time. *[[1911]] &ndash; The [[University of the Philippines College of Law]] is formally established; three future [[President of the Philippines|Philippine presidents]] are among the first enrollees. *[[1915]] &ndash; The [[United States House of Representatives]] rejects a proposal to require states to give [[women's suffrage|women the right to vote]]. *[[1916]] &ndash; Both [[Oswald Boelcke]] and [[Max Immelmann]], for achieving eight aerial victories each over [[Allies of World War I|Allied]] aircraft, receive the [[German Empire]]'s highest military award, the [[Pour le Mérite]] as the first German aviators to earn it. *[[1918]] &ndash; The [[Minnie Pit Disaster]] coal mining accident occurs in Halmer End, Staffordshire, in which 155 men and boys die. *[[1921]] &ndash; Acting to restore confidence in baseball after the [[Black Sox Scandal]], Judge [[Kenesaw Mountain Landis]] is elected as [[Major League Baseball]]'s first commissioner. *[[1932]] &ndash; [[Hattie Caraway]] becomes the first woman elected to the [[United States Senate]]. *[[1942]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: United States President [[Franklin D. Roosevelt]] creates the [[National War Labor Board (1942–1945)|National War Labor Board]]. *[[1945]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: The [[Red Army]] begins the [[Vistula–Oder Offensive]]. *[[1962]] &ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: [[Operation Chopper (Vietnam)|Operation Chopper]], the first American combat mission in the war, takes place. *[[1964]] &ndash; Rebels in [[Zanzibar]] begin a revolt known as the [[Zanzibar Revolution]] and proclaim a republic. *[[1966]] &ndash; [[Lyndon B. Johnson]] states that the United States should stay in [[South Vietnam]] until [[Communism|Communist]] aggression there is ended. *[[1967]] &ndash; Dr. [[James Bedford]] becomes the first person to be [[cryonics|cryonically preserved]] with intent of future resuscitation. *[[1969]] &ndash; The [[New York Jets]] of the [[American Football League]] defeat the [[History of the Baltimore Colts|Baltimore Colts]] of the [[National Football League]] to win [[Super Bowl III]] in what is considered to be one of the greatest upsets in sports history. *[[1970]] &ndash; [[Biafra]] capitulates, ending the [[Nigerian Civil War]]. *[[1971]] &ndash; The [[Harrisburg Seven]]: Rev. [[Philip Berrigan]] and five other activists are indicted on charges of conspiring to kidnap [[Henry Kissinger]] and of plotting to blow up the heating tunnels of federal buildings in [[Washington, D.C.]] *[[1976]] &ndash; The [[United Nations Security Council]] votes 11–1 to allow the [[Palestine Liberation Organization]] to participate in a Security Council debate (without voting rights). *[[1986]] &ndash; [[Space Shuttle program]]: Congressman [[Bill Nelson (politician)|Bill Nelson]] lifts off from [[Kennedy Space Center]] aboard [[Space Shuttle Columbia|''Columbia'']] on mission [[STS-61-C]] as a [[payload specialist]]. *[[1990]] &ndash; A [[Baku pogrom|seven-day pogrom]] breaks out against [[Armenians|the Armenian civilian population of Baku, Azerbaijan]], during which Armenians were beaten, tortured, murdered, and expelled from the city. *[[1991]] &ndash; [[Gulf War|Persian Gulf War]]: An act of the U.S. Congress authorizes the use of American military force to drive [[Ba'athist Iraq|Iraq]] out of [[Kuwait]]. *[[1998]] &ndash; Nineteen European nations agree to forbid [[human cloning]]. *[[2001]] &ndash; [[Downtown Disney (Disneyland Resort)|Downtown Disney]] opens to the public as part of the [[Disneyland Resort]] in [[Anaheim, California]]. *[[2004]] &ndash; The world's largest [[ocean liner]], {{RMS|Queen Mary 2}}, makes its maiden voyage. *[[2005]] &ndash; [[Deep Impact (spacecraft)|Deep Impact]] launches from [[Cape Canaveral]] on a [[Delta II]] rocket. *[[2006]] &ndash; [[Incidents during the Hajj|A stampede]] during the [[Stoning of the Devil]] ritual on the last day at the [[Hajj]] in [[Mina, Saudi Arabia]], kills at least 362 Muslim [[pilgrim]]s. *[[2010]] &ndash; An [[2010 Haiti earthquake|earthquake in Haiti]] occurs, killing over 100,000 people and destroying much of the capital [[Port-au-Prince]]. *[[2012]] &ndash; [[2012 Romanian protests|Violent protests]] occur in [[Bucharest]], [[Romania]], as two-day-old demonstrations continue against President [[Traian Băsescu]]'s economic [[austerity]] measures. Clashes are reported in numerous Romanian cities between protesters and law enforcement officers. *[[2015]] &ndash; [[January 2015 Kolofata raid|Government raids kill 143 Boko Haram fighters in Kolofata, Cameroon]]. *[[2016]] &ndash; Ten people are killed and 15 wounded in a [[January 2016 Istanbul bombing|bombing]] near the [[Sultan Ahmed Mosque|Blue Mosque in Istanbul]].
