ll (American musician)|Chris Bell]], American singer-songwriter and guitarist (d. 1978) * 1951 &ndash; [[Rush Limbaugh]], American talk show host and author * 1951 &ndash; [[Drew Pearson (American football)|Drew Pearson]], American football player and sportscaster *[[1952]] &ndash; [[Phil Perry]], American singer-songwriter and producer * 1952 &ndash; [[Ricky Van Shelton]], American country singer-songwriter and guitarist * 1952 &ndash; [[John Walker (runner)|John Walker]], New Zealand runner and politician * 1952 &ndash; [[Walter Mosley]], American novelist *[[1953]] &ndash; [[Mary Harron]], Canadian director and screenwriter *[[1954]] &ndash; [[Howard Stern]], American radio host, actor, and author * 1954 &ndash; [[Martin Kylhammar]], Swedish professor of culture and society *[[1955]] &ndash; [[Tom Ardolino]], American rock drummer ([[NRBQ]]) (d. 2012) *[[1956]] &ndash; [[Nikolai Noskov]], Russian rock singer and singer-songwriter *[[1957]] &ndash; [[John Lasseter]], American animator, director, and producer * 1957 &ndash; [[Jeremy Sams]], English director, playwright, and composer *[[1958]] &ndash; [[Christiane Amanpour]], English-born Iranian-American journalist * 1958 &ndash; [[Curt Fraser]], American-Canadian ice hockey player and coach *[[1959]] &ndash; [[B. Brian Blair]], American wrestler and politician * 1959 &ndash; [[Per Gessle]], Swedish singer-songwriter, guitarist, and producer *[[1960]] &ndash; [[Oliver Platt]], Canadian-American actor * 1960 &ndash; [[Dominique Wilkins]], French-American basketball player and manager *[[1961]] &ndash; [[Simon Russell Beale]], Malaysia-born English actor and historian *[[1962]] &ndash; [[Joe Quesada]], American author and illustrator * 1962 &ndash; [[Richie Richardson]], Antiguan cricketer * 1962 &ndash; [[Luna Vachon]], American-Canadian wrestler and manager (d. 2010) *[[1963]] &ndash; [[François Girard]], Canadian director and screenwriter * 1963 &ndash; [[Nando Reis]], Brazilian singer-songwriter, guitarist, and p